# Steps to reproduce

```                    
        public void Process(out string error)
        {
            using (var ps = PowerShell.Create())
            {
                ps.AddScript("Get-Module -ListAvailable -Name MSOnline");

                var results = ps.Invoke();

                if (results.Count == 0)
                {
                    error = "You do not have the PowerShell MSOnline module installed.  Please run Install-Module MSOnline in PowerShell, then restart this app.";
                }
                else
                {
                    error = null;
                }
            }
        }

```

I can run the same command directly in PowerShell & it lists MSOnline without an issue.  However, when run from within my .NET project, I get nothing.

I have NuGet packages installed:
Microsoft.PowerShell.SDK 6.2.0
Microsoft.PowerShell.Commands.Diagnostics 6.2.0
Microsoft.WSMan.Management 6.2.0

I have also attempted this in a clean console application with the above code only, on another machine and see the same results!

# Expected behavior

Results should contain one result listing MSOnline.

# Actual behavior

Results is an empty collection

# Steps to reproduce

```powershell
Add-Type -TypeDefinition '
    public struct MyStruct
    {
        public int X;

        public MyStruct(int x) => X = x;

        public static void AlterStructs(ref MyStruct s1, ref MyStruct s2)
        {
            s1.X += 10;
            s2.X += 10;
        }

        public static int WorkingExample()
        {
            var myStruct = new MyStruct(10);
            AlterStructs(ref myStruct, ref myStruct);
            return myStruct.X;
        }
    }'

$myStruct = [MyStruct]::new(10)
[MyStruct]::AlterStructs([ref] $myStruct, [ref] $myStruct)
```

# Expected behavior

```powershell
PS> $myStruct.X
30
PS> [MyStruct]::WorkingExample()
30
```

# Actual behavior

```powershell
PS> $myStruct.X
20
PS> [MyStruct]::WorkingExample()
30
```

